	  "name": "Sequester",
	  "description": "By means of this spell, a willing creature or an object can be hidden away, safe from detection for the duration. When you cast the spell and touch the target, it becomes invisible and cant be targeted by divination spells or perceived through scrying sensors created by divination spells.If the target is a creature, it falls into a state of suspended animation. Time ceases to flow for it, and it doesnt grow older.You can set a condition for the spell to end early. The condition can be anything you choose, but it must occur or be visible within 1 mile of the target. Examples include after 1,000 years or when the tarrasque awakens. This spell also ends if the target takes any damage.",
